📊 Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA) Project

This project focuses on performing Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA) on a dataset to uncover hidden patterns, identify trends, detect anomalies, and generate meaningful insights through statistical analysis and data visualization.

🚀 Project Overview

The primary goal of this project is to understand the dataset before applying any machine learning models. EDA helps in identifying data quality issues, handling missing values, understanding feature distributions, discovering relationships between variables, and extracting actionable insights.

📌 Key Tasks Performed
Data Loading and Inspection
Data Cleaning and Preprocessing
Handling Missing Values
Duplicate Data Detection and Removal
Statistical Summary Analysis
Outlier Detection
Univariate Analysis
Bivariate Analysis
Correlation Analysis
Feature Distribution Analysis
Data Visualization using various plots
📊 Visualizations Used
Histograms
Bar Charts
Pie Charts
Scatter Plots
Box Plots
Count Plots
Heatmaps
Pair Plots
Correlation Matrix
🛠️ Technologies Used
Python
Pandas
NumPy
Matplotlib
Seaborn
Jupyter Notebook
🔍 Analysis Highlights
Identified missing and inconsistent values within the dataset.
Explored feature distributions and data patterns.
Analyzed correlations between variables using heatmaps.
Detected and visualized outliers using boxplots.
Generated statistical summaries to understand dataset characteristics.
Created insightful visualizations for better decision-making.
📈 Outcome

The analysis provides a comprehensive understanding of the dataset and serves as a foundation for feature engineering, machine learning model building, and data-driven decision-making.

